# PocketBase Development Configuration
# This file shows the structure for environment-specific configuration.
# 
# ENVIRONMENT-SPECIFIC CONFIG:
# Copy .env.dev and .env.test to customize environment-specific settings.
# Each environment (dev/test) has its own configuration file:
#   .env.dev  - Development environment settings
#   .env.test - Test environment settings
#
# GLOBAL CONFIG:
# Copy this file to .env.local for global overrides.
# 
# VERSION PINNING:
# PocketBase version is managed via .pb-version file (similar to .node-version)
# Change the version in .pb-version and run ./pb.sh install to upgrade

# Example environment-specific settings (see .env.dev and .env.test):
# ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com
# ADMIN_PASSWORD=admin123456
# USER_EMAIL=user@example.com
# USER_PASSWORD=userpass123
# PORT=8090
# PB_HOST=127.0.0.1

# Global overrides (uncomment to override environment-specific settings):
# PB_HOST=127.0.0.1
# ADMIN_EMAIL=custom-admin@example.com
